&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;NHS 111 Wales Cwmbran Gwent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Clinical Advisor - Paramedics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you ready for a new direction in your Nursing/Paramedic career and a new exciting challenge? Would you like to work in a fast paced environment using your clinical knowledge to provide excellent care to patients through telephone triage?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Welsh Ambulance Service is currently recruiting experienced registered (General / Children’s) Nurses and Paramedics to work in its Clinical Contact Centre in Cwmbran as part of the team providing &#39;hear and treat&#39; services for both NHS Direct Wales and 111 services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working as a Clinical Advisor gives you the opportunity to develop your clinical assessment skills for a wide variety of patients from whom we receive excellent feedback on the service provided.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are keen to hear from experienced Band 5 nurses whom are now ready to progress their career or from existing Band 6 Nurses/Paramedics whom are ready for a new challenge. The service is busiest during evenings/weekends so we are seeking individuals whom are able to work during these hours.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In exchange we can offer a range of contracted hours per week, a comprehensive training programme which supports revalidation requirements and on-going support from our experienced team of practice coaches and clinical team leaders.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Induction training for this post will include an initial 5 week fulltime programme which will be a combination of office hours and shift work. Following a period of consolidation of practise, a further 2 weeks of training will be undertaken.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are in the process of establishing an exciting initiative that will support clinicians working from home.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date: 10th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;N.B. THERE ARE POSTS ADVERTISED FOR PARAMEDICS AND NURSES. PLEASE ENSURE YOU APPLY TO THE RELEVANT ADVERT - 020-NMR026-1020.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sandra Pollard, Clinical Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;tel: 01633 626301 /03&lt;/p&gt;
